THE Akwa Ibom State chapter of the All Progressives Congress, has said it has uncovered a plot to destabilise the party with the aid of a fake video clip being circulated by unknown persons with intent to cause disharmony in the party. State Publicity Secretary of the party, Mr Nkereuwem Enyongekere, said this in a statement titled, ‘An advisory: Plan to cause disharmony in APC.’ He alleged that the masterminds of the plot have recirculated a video clip of an illegal APC stakeholders meeting which was held on Sunday, March 28,2021 to further their motives According to him, a highly credible source had revealed that attempts have been made to induce ward chairmen and other party leaders to incite a revolt in the APC family. The statement read in part, “A clandestine plan by sponsored members of the party to cause disharmony in the APC has been exposed. “Information from a highly credible source has revealed that attempts to use monetary inducements to recruit some ward chairmen and other party organs to incite and cause a revolt in our very peaceful APC family by the perpetrators has been exposed. “Be informed that the video clip and its audio is misleading and full of misinformation.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com